### Footnotes

<span id="fn_790"></span>[172:1](jub69.htm#fr_798.md) Cf. Gen. xlvi. 10.
According to xxx. 7 ff. such a marriage (with a Canaanitish woman) was
punishable with death.

<span id="fn_791"></span>[172:2](jub69.htm#fr_799.md) Cf. *Test. Levi* xi.
i.

<span id="fn_792"></span>[172:3](jub69.htm#fr_800.md) Cf. xli. 7. The name
goes back to "Bath-shua" (*i. e.* "daughter of Shua"); cf. *Test. Judah*
viii. 2, etc.; cf. Gen. xxxviii. 2.

<span id="fn_793"></span>[172:4](jub69.htm#fr_801.md) The name is doubtful.
Some Ethiopic MSS. omit it.

<span id="fn_794"></span>[172:5](jub69.htm#fr_802.md) Cf. Gen. xli. 45.

